Privacy Policy – Showoff
Last Updated: 2026-01-12

This Privacy Policy describes how Showoff collects, uses, and stores information when you use the Showoff Twitch Extension and related services.

1. Basis of data processing
We process personal data in accordance with applicable data protection regulations, in particular the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR).

Data is processed based on:
Your consent (Article 6 (1) (a) GDPR),
The performance of the service requested by you (Article 6 (1) (b) GDPR),
Compliance with legal obligations (Article 6 (1) (c) GDPR),
Our legitimate interests in operating and securing the service (Article 6 (1) (f) GDPR).

2. What data we process
We process only the data necessary to operate the Showoff extension.

Twitch information
Twitch User ID
Twitch Username
Twitch Channel ID
Extension-related data
Viewer participation data within a channel
Streamer configuration data (collections, cards, settings)
Feature and configuration state

We do not collect email addresses, real names, physical addresses, phone numbers, payment information, or advertising identifiers.

3. Purpose of processing
We use this information solely to:
Provide and operate the Showoff extension
Enable viewer–streamer interaction
Store and apply streamer configuration
Maintain security and correct functionality

We do not use data for advertising, profiling, or analytics.

We may use cookies or similar technical mechanisms only where required for basic service functionality, security, or configuration persistence.

4. Data retention

We retain personal data only for as long as necessary to operate the Showoff extension or fulfill legal obligations.
When data is no longer required, it is deleted or anonymized. Where immediate deletion is not technically possible (for example, backups), the data is securely stored and isolated until deletion is possible.

5. Data security

We apply appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect the personal data we process. However, no method of electronic transmission or storage can be guaranteed to be completely secure. Use of the service is at your own risk.

6. User rights

You have the right to:

Request access to your personal data
Request correction of inaccurate data
Request deletion or restriction of processing
Receive a copy of your personal data in a structured, machine-readable format
Withdraw consent where processing is based on consent
Lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority

You may exercise these rights by contacting us at:
playshowoff@gmail.com

7. Third-party platforms

Showoff operates within Twitch’s platform and relies on Twitch APIs and services. We do not control Twitch’s data practices. Please review Twitch’s Privacy Policy to understand how they collect and process personal data.

8. Changes to this policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to remain compliant with applicable laws. The latest version will always be indicated by the “Last Updated” date above.

9. Contact

If you have questions or requests regarding this Privacy Policy, please contact:
playshowoff@gmail.com
